{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd07-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4087"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4087"},"text":"§ 4087.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Termination of residential or motor vehicle leases and telephone service contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The terms governing the termination of residential or motor vehicle leases and telephone service contracts described in sections 305 and 305A, respectively, of the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3955"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 3955","children":[],"tail":" and 3956) with respect to servicemembers who receive military orders described in such Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3901"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 3901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall apply in the same manner and to the same extent to members of the Foreign Service who are posted in the United States or posted abroad in accordance with this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd08-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465/tI/s907"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465, title I, § 907","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/dF/tLXII/s6207/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, div. F, title LXII, § 6207(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/2392"},"text":"135 Stat. 2392","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/dG/tLXXI/s7110"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, div. G, title LXXI, § 7110","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/2526"},"text":"138 Stat. 2526","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id9069fd09-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id9069fd0a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id9069fd0b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Servicemembers Civil Relief Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-17/ch888"},"text":"act Oct. 17, 1940, ch. 888","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/1178"},"text":"54 Stat. 1178","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 50 (§ 3901 et seq.) of Title 50, War and National Defense. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3901"},"text":"section 3901 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2071"},"text":"94 Stat. 2071","children":[],"tail":", known as the Foreign Service Act of 1980, which is classified principally to this chapter (§ 3901 et seq.). For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s3901"},"text":"section 3901 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id9069fd0c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Foreign Service who are posted in the United States or posted abroad” for “Service who are posted abroad at a Foreign Service post”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
